  "local_port": 46182,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "Finding quality beef jerky and biltong in London is easier than ever, thanks to a variety of supermarkets, specialty stores, and online retailers offering these delicious, protein-packed snacks. Here are some top options to consider:\n\n### **Supermarkets**\n- **Waitrose**: Offers a selection of premium beef jerky in their snacks aisle. Look for brands like Jack Link's or local artisanal options.\n- **Sainsbury\u2019s**: Selected larger stores stock beef jerky and occasionally biltong. Check the international or snack sections.\n- **Marks & Spencer**: Known for high-quality food products, M&S often carries beef jerky in their snack range.\n- **Tesco**: Larger Tesco Express and Superstores may have beef jerky available, especially in the international foods section.\n\n### **Specialty Stores & Butchers**\n- **Butchers at Borough Market**: Various artisanal butchers here offer homemade beef jerky and sometimes biltong. It's a great place to find fresh, high-quality options.\n- **The Biltong Box**: Although primarily an online retailer, they often collaborate with local stores for pop-up events and tastings.\n- **Planet Organic**: This health-focused store often stocks a range of dried meats, including beef jerky and biltong, suitable for different dietary preferences.\n- **Harrods Food Hall**: For premium and gourmet beef jerky options, Harrods offers a selection that caters to discerning tastes.\n\n### **Online Retailers**\n- **Amazon UK**: A wide variety of beef jerky and biltong brands are available with customer reviews to help you choose.\n- **The Biltong Co**: Specializes in authentic South African biltong delivered directly to your door.\n- **JerkyOnline.co.uk**: Offers a broad selection of beef jerky flavors and styles, including gluten-free and low-sugar options.\n- **Biltong Box**: Provides subscription services for regular deliveries of biltong, ensuring you never run out of your favorite snack.\n\n### **Ethnic and International Stores**\n- **South African Stores**: Areas with a significant South African community, such as parts of West London, may have specialized stores selling authentic biltong.\n- **African Markets**: Some African grocery stores and markets carry biltong alongside other traditional snacks.\n\n### **High-End and Gourmet Shops**\n- **Selfridges Food Hall**: Occasionally features gourmet beef jerky and biltong, perfect for gifts or indulging yourself.\n- **Fortnum & Mason**: Known for luxury foods, they may offer gourmet dried meats during certain seasons or as part of their gourmet snack selection.\n\n### **Tips for Finding the Best Products**\n- **Check Reviews**: Whether shopping online or in-store, look for customer reviews to ensure quality and taste.\n- **Ask for Samples**: In specialty butchers and markets, don\u2019t hesitate to ask for samples to find your preferred flavor and texture.\n- **Look for Artisanal Brands**: Smaller, artisanal producers often use higher quality meats and offer unique seasoning blends.\n\n### **Popular Brands to Look For**\n- **Jack Link\u2019s**: Widely available and offers a variety of flavors.\n- **Krave**: Known for gourmet jerky with unique seasoning profiles.\n- **The Biltong Company**: Specializes in authentic biltong with various cuts and flavors.\n- **Perky Jerky**: Offers both traditional beef jerky and biltong options.\n\nLondon's diverse and vibrant food scene ensures that you can find both traditional beef jerky and authentic biltong to satisfy your cravings. Whether you prefer to shop in person or conveniently online, there's something to suit every taste and preference.",
